slf4j internally will check the log level, so checking log level is not needed in this case.
checking log level is needed only when the information needed to be logged requires some pre-computation. For example in the following case checking log level helps:
// checking log level helps
if (logger.isDebugEnabled()) {
 String diagnosticsInfoAsString = diagnosticsInfo.toJson()
 logger.debug("diagnostics info is {}, diagnosticsInfoAsString);
}
but here it is not needed
// checking log level is not needed as no pre-computation is done here.
// slf4 will do internal checking.
logger.debug("endpoint is {}, endpoint);
